## VALIDATION SCRIPTS

```bash
# Pre-commit checks
node scripts/validation/check-await-without-async.js    # await in non-async functions
node scripts/validation/check-database-routing.js       # orphaned DB entries
node scripts/validation/check-mfr-config-completeness.js # missing per-MFR configs
node scripts/validation/check-fingerprint-health.js     # collisions + format + wildcards
node scripts/validation/cross-category-collision-gate.js # cross-driver collisions

# Automation
node scripts/automation/smart-driver-adaptation.js       # MFR database updater (weekly)
node scripts/community-sync/sync-all.js                  # Z2M/Johan/GitHub sync

# SDK3 validation
npx homey app validate --level publish                  # full SDK3 validation
npx homey app compose                                   # regenerate app.json from compose
node -c <file.js>                                       # syntax check
```

---

## GIT WORKFLOW

- Commit format: `type: description` (feat/fix/docs/refactor)
- NEVER `npx homey app publish` locally — use GitHub Actions
- ALWAYS `git pull --rebase origin master` before push
- CI validates via `PRE_COMMIT_CHECKS.js` before push
- Branch separation: master = beta, stable-v5 = production

---

## ISSUE PROTOCOL

- NEVER close issues without user confirmation (Rule from PROJECT_INDEX.md §30)
- Auto-close template: version, root cause, files modified, test instructions
- Re-open if user reports issue persists
- Cross-reference with Z2M/ZHA source code for DP mappings
- Check `scripts/data/z2m-data.json` for Z2M DP definitions

---

## BIDIRECTIONAL BUTTONS

- PhysicalButtonMixin: per-gang state, 2000ms timeout, flow cards physical only
- VirtualButtonMixin: `markAppCommand()` BEFORE device command
- Anti-patterns to AVOID:
  - Local `_markAppCommand()` that doesn't call `super.markAppCommand()`
  - `getTriggerCard()` without `.trigger()` call
  - `initPhysicalButtonDetection()` called twice (first without args)
  - `onDeleted()` without `clearTimeout()` or `super.onDeleted()`

---

## TUYA DP BATTERY DEVICES

- Battery devices (receiveWhenIdle=false) do NOT send data spontaneously
- MUST use `requestDP(dp)` to query — Z2M/ZHA "spell_data_query" pattern
- 5-method fallback chain: raw frame → cluster.dataQuery → command → magic packet → raw magic
- DP4 battery: Some variants send 0/1 instead of percentage — handle in `_handleBatteryDP` override
- Do NOT put DP4 in dpMappings if override is needed — parent class skips override

---

## SECURITY

- NEVER token in `.git/config` (Rule R1)
- NEVER `.env` in repo (Rule R2)
- NEVER `process.env.CLIENT_ID/SECRET` in runtime (Rule R3)
- Run `npm run security-scan` before push
